.TH "cpufreq_remove_update_util_hook" 9 "cpufreq_remove_update_util_hook" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
cpufreq_remove_update_util_hook \- Clear the CPU's update_util_data pointer.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" cpufreq_remove_update_util_hook
.BI "(int cpu "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "cpu" 12
The CPU to clear the pointer for.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Clear the update_util_data pointer for the given CPU.

Callers must use RCU callbacks to free any memory that might be
accessed via the old update_util_data pointer or invoke \fBsynchronize_rcu\fP
right after this function to avoid use-after-free.
